The evidence shows a single snapshot of your project portfolio: 8 projects across Python, TypeScript, and Rust, spanning different architectures (APIs, SPAs, CLI tools, libraries, workspaces). You're converging on shared technologies in some areas—Python across Friday variants and finance-tracker; TypeScript/React/Supabase across MindWell and vivaha.

However, the system explicitly notes: "Long-term engineering trends cannot yet be determined because only one observation exists. They will appear after more `friday observe` runs."

Trends require multiple observations over time to show velocity, adoption patterns, technical debt accumulation, or strategic shifts. A single state snapshot shows what exists, not how it's evolving. Run `friday observe` periodically, and patterns will emerge—which technologies are gaining or losing adoption, which projects are accelerating or stalling, whether architectural decisions are converging or diverging.
